Author: McDougall, Keith L. ‘Aerial Photographic Interpretation of Vegetation Changes on the Bogong High Plains, Victoria, between 1936 and 1980’. Australian Journal of Botany 51, no. 3 (2003): 251. https://doi.org/10.1071/BT02079.
Study details: Pairwise. Two repeat photos 1939 and 1980. Aerial photos overlaid on a grid (30m x 30m) and the proportion of ecosystem counted for each grid. Total number of grid cells = N, = 13849
Other?: Hydroelectric plant caused flooding / disturbance to area 1950s, these are visible in 1980s photos.

Author: McDougall, Keith L. ‘Aerial Photographic Interpretation of Vegetation Changes on the Bogong High Plains, Victoria, between 1936 and 1980’. Australian Journal of Botany 51, no. 3 (2003): 251. https://doi.org/10.1071/BT02079.
Study details: Pairwise. Two repeat photos 1939 and 1980. Aerial photos overlaid on a grid (30m x 30m) and the proportion of ecosystem counted for each grid. Total number of grid cells = N, = 13849
Other?: Hydroelectric plant caused flooding / disturbance to area 1950s, these are visible in 1980s photos.
Old.Response: Open heathland (Asterolasia trymalioides, Grevillea australis, Leucopogon hookeri)

Author: McDougall, Keith L. ‘Aerial Photographic Interpretation of Vegetation Changes on the Bogong High Plains, Victoria, between 1936 and 1980’. Australian Journal of Botany 51, no. 3 (2003): 251. https://doi.org/10.1071/BT02079.
Study details: Pairwise. Two repeat photos 1939 and 1980. Aerial photos overlaid on a grid (30m x 30m) and the proportion of ecosystem counted for each grid. Total number of grid cells = N, = 13849
Other?: Hydroelectric plant caused flooding / disturbance to area 1950s, these are visible in 1980s photos.
Old.Response: Heathland (wet) (dominant Epacris glacialis, Epacris paludosa, Richea continentis)
